        "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mggmgi1a/b230698c-db25-4d96-bb98-84baa6849e49/3bc576e0-a385-11f0-b4ef-8bc37809d563/file-jaoe38c1mggmgi1b.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mggmgi1a/b230698c-db25-4d96-bb98-84baa6849e49/3bc576e0-a385-11f0-b4ef-8bc37809d563/file-jaoe38c1mggmgi1b.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2007 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 8 English Option 3\">",
        "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mggmhdj5/94331f76-12dd-492f-959b-ad0f2ea0f603/5419f310-a385-11f0-b4ef-8bc37809d563/file-jaoe38c1mggmhdj6.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mggmhdj5/94331f76-12dd-492f-959b-ad0f2ea0f603/5419f310-a385-11f0-b4ef-8bc37809d563/file-jaoe38c1mggmhdj6.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2007 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 8 English Option 4\">"
      ],
      "correctOption": 1,
      "solution": "<p>Concentrated HNO$$_3$$ and concentrated H$$_2$$SO$$_4$$ will cause nitration of the ring to introduce $$-$$NO$$_2$$ in one of the rings.</p>\n<p>The ring which is adjacent to N atom is more electron rich than the other. This is due to +R effect of NH group.</p>\n<p>Further, it will attack on more activated ortho or para positions. Since, ortho attack is not possible due to bulky ring present adjacent to it, there will be an attack on para position.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mggmk29t/be01db2d-b8a8-4aec-89d0-affdadbea966/9ed4cf10-a385-11f0-b4ef-8bc37809d563/file-jaoe38c1mggmk29u.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mggmk29t/be01db2d-b8a8-4aec-89d0-affdadbea966/9ed4cf10-a385-11f0-b4ef-8bc37809d563/file-jaoe38c1mggmk29u.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2007 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 8 English Explanation\"></p>",
      "marks": 3,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "topic": "Hydrocarbon"
    },
